meta.name: Deal or No Deal
meta.description: Deal or No Deal, the exhilarating hit game show where contestants must beat the Banker to win a huge cash prize of $100,000, is making a triumphant return to 10 and 10 Play.Hosted by TV Week Gold Logie award winner Grant Denyer, every episode is a high-pressure, high-stakes game of risk versus reward in which contestants face a series of potentially life-altering decisions.

videos.title: Episode 84
videos.overview: Retired newsagent Darren has spent his career watching customers win millions. Now it's his turn to flip the script and win big, hoping to help set his daughter up for life.

videos.title: Episode 85
videos.overview: Impractical Joker Dom Littrich loves a cheeky prank, but can he pull one over on The Banker and win 100K for his charity Beyond Blue.

videos.title: Episode 86
videos.overview: Cool mum Kate Weidman holds the record for being the biggest baby born in a Singaporean hospital. Now she is aiming to break another record by winning 100K on The Deal.

videos.title: Episode 137
videos.overview: Before he takes a brand-new batch of celebs on a race around the world in the upcoming Amazing Race Australia: Celebrity Edition, Beau Ryan graces the Deal or No Deal arena, ready to find the amazing case, which could see him win a whopping $100,000 for charity.Taking on the Banker for a very good cause, Beau will be hoping to win big for his chosen charity, the Helping Hearts Foundation. The organisation is focused on educating Australians, with the intent to increase survival rates of people who experience sudden cardiac arrest.

videos.title: Episode 141
videos.overview: They're the hilarious brothers who have blown up all over social media, and now Luke and Sassy' Scott O'Halloran are taking on the Deal or No Deal Banker.With over five million followers on social media, the brothers have been sharing hilarious content for years, with their relatable pranks and sibling rivalries earning them a massive online audience. Turning their content into a successful podcast, the brothers are now taking on the world of TV.Ahead of their upcoming adventure on The Amazing Race Australia: Celebrity Edition, Luke and Scott are making a pitstop at The Deal in the hopes of winning up to $100,000 for their chosen charity: The Royal Children's Hospital Good Friday Appeal.
